# Maven ignorant of minimum-Java-version requirements

&gt;  I want to downgrade spring-cloud-config-server to match jdk 15

Maven cannot do that for you, not automatically. Maven is completely ignorant of any particular dependency’s requirement regarding a version of Java. 

Minimum-Java-version checking *would* be a neat feature. But that is currently not currently in the scope of Maven. 

You will need to do the research to discover what version of your needed library/framework will work with your chosen version of Java. 

Once you have learned the necessary version, you *can* specify that version number in your Maven POM. To specify a version, use the `&lt;version&gt;` element.


```xml
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.cloud&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-cloud-config-server&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;1.8.0.10&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;
```

